docs.text: " jack frost , " is one of those dumb , corny concoctions that attempts to be a heartwarming family film , but is too muddled in its own cliches and predictability to be the least bit touching .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: this does not come as a surprise , since the studio that made it is warner brothers , who is on a current streak of one bad film after the other .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: jack frost ( michael keaton ) is a struggling middle-aged rock musician who loves his wife , gabby ( kelly preston ) , and 11-year-old son , charlie ( joseph cross ) , but doesn't spend nearly enough time with them .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: when he receives a call from a music label that wants to hear him play , he has to cancel his planned family outing up in the mountains for christmas .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: halfway there , jack has second thoughts , but on his way back home , is in a car accident and dies .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: switch forward a year , christmas is approaching once again , and charlie and gabby are still having a difficult time coming to terms with jack's death .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: when charlie begins to play the harmonica his father gave him the night before he died , the snowman outside the house is taken over by jack's spirit .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: jack wants to spend some time with his son before the upcoming warm front melts him , but charlie desperately tries to prevent his melting demise .

docs.text: " frosty the snowman , " is a classic cartoon , and the idea of a snowman that is alive works splendidly when animated , but as a live-action film , it doesn't work at all .

docs.text: after a somewhat promising prologue in which the frost family is established , " jack frost , " quickly goes downhill , especially once the snowman comes into play .

docs.text: since jack has been deceased for a whole year , you would think there would be many questions to ask him , such as , " what happens after you die ? "

docs.text: but instead , the film focuses on a snowball fight subplot and an inevitably oversentimental climax that could be telegraphed before i even sat down to watch the movie .
